        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="grid-2">
                <div>
                    <h3>Bubble Sort O(n²)</h3>
                    <p>Repeatedly swaps adjacent elements if they are wrong. "Bubbles" largest to the end.</p>
                    <pre><code class="python">def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        swapped = False
        # Last i elements are already sorted
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
                swapped = True
        if not swapped:
            break</code></pre>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3>Selection Sort O(n²)</h3>
                    <p>Finds the minimum element and moves it to the sorted part.</p>
                    <pre><code class="python">def selection_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        min_idx = i
        for j in range(i+1, n):
            if arr[j] < arr[min_idx]:
                min_idx = j
        # Swap found min with first
        arr[i], arr[min_idx] = arr[min_idx], arr[i]</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Quick Sort O(n log n)</h3>
            <p>Divide and conquer using a pivot. Much faster for large datasets.</p>
            <pre><code class="python">def quick_sort(arr):
    if len(arr) <= 1: return arr
    pivot = arr[len(arr) // 2]
    left = [x for x in arr if x < pivot]
    middle = [x for x in arr if x == pivot]
    right = [x for x in arr if x > pivot]
    return quick_sort(left) + middle + quick_sort(right)</code></pre>
        </div>
    </section>

